          </p>

          <p>
            Most recently, <a
              href="/books/when-the-naughty-step-makes-things-worse"
              >When the Naughty Step Makes Things Worse</a
            > (with Eliza Fricker) addresses something which had bothered me for
            a while – what happens when conventional parenting strategies result
            in parent and child being locked into battles? Often parents are told
            to just keep trying, and this book offers something different.
          </p>

          <p>
            Parents would often ask me whether there was anything for their
            teenagers when they had stopped going to school which didn’t assume
            that going back to school was the only answer. I couldn’t find
            anything, and so Eliza Fricker and I wrote one. <a
              href="/books/the-teenagers-guide-to-burnout"
              >The Teenager’s Guide to Burnout</a
            > is an illustrated guide for teens on finding their way back to the
            life they want to lead.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div> -->
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">
    <span class="courses-section-title">Featured Courses</span>
  </h2>
  <CoursesList
    courses={featuredCourses1}
    categoryId="featured"
    categoryName="Featured Courses"
  />
</BaseLayout>
<style lang="scss">
  /*Styles to be moved into component files  */
  /* Courses h1 */
  h1 {
    font-family: Oswald;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 46px;
    line-height: 56px;
  }

  .breadcrumb-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    font-family: sans-serif;
    width: 100%;
    .ol {
      width: 100%;
      align-items: flex-start;
      text-align: left;
    }
  }

  .breadcrumb ol {
    display: flex;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 32px 0 0 0;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .breadcrumb li {
    font-family: Oswald;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 24px;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    a,
    a:visited,
    a:active,
    a:hover {
      color: var(--brand-primary);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
  }

  .breadcrumb li + li::before {
    content: "/";
    padding: 0 8px;
    color: #6c757d;
  }
</style>
